{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17641594","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17641594"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:29:46+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:29:46+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17891"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17891","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17891"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.43,0.05,0.52,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10605"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114659"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10605","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10605"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17891"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96662"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"10025"},{"type":"tags","id":"10053"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24714"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24717"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114659","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/114659"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe body undertakes several physiological changes in the fasting state.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following processes do fatty acids in the liver undergo during fasting?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Protein synthesis","Oxidation","VLDL synthesis","Ketone body production","Glycogen synthesis"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EKetone body production\u003C/strong\u003E, also known as ketogenesis, occurs when the liver processes fatty acids into ketone bodies, serving as an alternative energy source, particularly for the brain, during periods of low glucose availability.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOxidation\u003C/strong\u003E of fatty acids provides the energy required for gluconeogenesis and ketogenesis, but the primary purpose of fatty acid utilisation in the liver during fasting is to produce ketone bodies.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVLDL synthesis\u003C/strong\u003E involves the packaging of triglycerides and cholesterol for transport in the bloodstream. This is not the primary function of fatty acids during fasting.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGlycogen synthesis\u003C/strong\u003E is not a process that occurs during fasting, as glycogen stores are depleted, and the body relies on gluconeogenesis and ketogenesis for energy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProtein synthesis\u003C/strong\u003E is not directly related to the utilisation of fatty acids during fasting. Instead, protein breakdown may occur to provide substrates for gluconeogenesis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["During fasting, the liver uses fatty acids primarily for ketone body production.","Ketone bodies are an important energy source during prolonged fasting, especially for the brain.","Fatty acid oxidation in the liver provides the energy required for gluconeogenesis and ketogenesis."],"references":["Hall JE. Guyton and Hall Textbook of Medical Physiology. 14th ed. Philadelphia: Elsevier; 2021. Chapter 69, pg. 858.","Bender, D. A., \u0026 Cunningham, S. M. (2021). Introduction to nutrition and metabolism. CRC Press","Salway, J. G. (2016). Metabolism at a Glance. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Judge A, Dodd MS. Metabolism. Essays Biochem. 2020 Oct 8;64(4):607-647. doi: 10.1042/EBC20190041. PMID: 32830223; PMCID: PMC7545035","Wang Y, Wu R. The Effect of Fasting on Human Metabolism and Psychological Health. Dis Markers. 2022 Jan 5;2022:5653739. doi: 10.1155/2022/5653739. PMID: 35035610; PMCID: PMC8754590","Nakrani MN, Wineland RH, Anjum F. Physiology, Glucose Metabolism. 2023 Jul 17. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32809434"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96662"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17891"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96662","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/96662"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-18T14:50:15+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-18T14:50:15+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10605"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114659"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4928","links":